oai_dc:dc.dc:title: A NUMERICAL MODEL OF WAVE/BREAKWATER INTERACTIONS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Austin, D. Ian
Schlueter, Roger S.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: numerical model
breakwater
wave/breakwater interaction
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A numerical model has been developed to simulate breakwater response to wave impacts with special reference to armor unit behavior and breakwater stability. The model uses a finite difference hydrodynamic code to follow the wave impacts and determine wave forces upon the breakwater components. A discrete element code models the breakwater response and motions. The model rationale and numerical basis are followed by three examples used in this, the concept validation, stage of model development.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 18 (1982): Proceedings of 18th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Cape Town, South Africa, 1982.; 124
